                        <interp inst="t18650918-name-400" type="surname" value="FLETCHER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650918-name-400" type="given" value="FREDERICK WILLIAM"></interp>FREDERICK WILLIAM FLETCHER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a commission merchant, Union Chambers, Old Broad-street—I am the publisher of the "London Trade Directory"—a book called "Wilson's Tales of the Borders," is issued with that directory—I employed the prisoner to obtain orders for me, and supplied him with forms for that purpose—this is one of the forms (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)—his duty was to get advertisements for the book, and to get these orders signed—I paid him a commission of 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on each—this order purports to be signed by "M. Hare," Stationer, High-street, Peckham—the prisoner has been paid his commission on this order.</p>
